  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA223-kiḷavi">itu pakaṟkuṟi vantu mīḷvāṉait tōḻi yiravukkuṟi nērvāḷ pōṉṟatuvu maṟuttu varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante seemingly granted a night tryst to the one who returned after having come for the day tryst [and] how she refused that too [and] urged for marriage.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA223">
<l>            ivaṭaṉ</l>
<l>            kāmam perumaiyiṟ kālaiyeṉ ṉāṇi</l>
<l>            ṉaṉpuperi tuṭaimaiyi ṉaḷittal vēṇṭip</l>
<l>            pakalum varuti palpūṅ kāṉa</l>
<l>            liṉṉī rākalō viṉitā leṉiṉiva</l>
<l>            ḷalari ṉaruṅkaṭip paṭukuva ḷataṉā </l>
<l>            lelli vammō mellam pulampa</l>
<l>            cuṟaviṉaṅ kalitta niṟaiyirum parappiṟ</l>
<l>            ṟuṟaiyiṉun tuñcāk kaṇṇar</l>
<l>            peṇṭiru muṭaittiv vampa lūrē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent">Since she, who does not tell the time because of the greatness</l>
<l rend="indent2">of her own desire,</l>
<l rend="indent">needs pitying because you possess so much love,<note place="foot">The line of argument in line 1-3 is a little bit odd. It ought to be the other way round: since HE comes even at midday SHE has to be pitied. Or should we think about taking <term xml:lang="ta">vēṇṭi</term> not as the usual absolutive, but as another 2nd sg., this time conveying a demand ("you ought to pity her")?</note></l>
<l>you want to come even at midday.</l>
<l rend="indent4">When she says “[it] is sweet indeed</l>
<l rend="indent">that you are like that, in the many-flowered seashore grove,”</l>
<l>because of the gossip she will be under severe protection.</l>
<l rend="indent3">Therefore,</l>
<l>please come at night, o tender man from the lonely [shore].</l>
<l rend="indent">More than the ghat with [its] full dark extension</l>
<l rend="indent2">where groups of sharks have been flourishing,</l>
<l>this talkative village possesses women too, with sleepless eyes.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
